{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>The family of type 2 integral membrane protein (ITM2) consists of three members, ITM2A, ITM2B and ITM2C [[cite:PUB00090586]]. Members of this family contain a BRICHOS domain, which possesses chaperone activity [[cite:PUB00090587], [cite:PUB00090588]].</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>ITM2A is a target gene of GATA-3, a T cell-specific transcription factor [[cite:PUB00090589]].</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ITM2B is proteolytically cleaved at three locations; cleavage by furin in the C-terminal region generates a 23-residue peptide (ABri23), processing by ADAM10 results in release of the BRICHOS domain from the membrane-bound N-terminal part and intramembrane cleavage by SPPL2a/2b liberates the intracellular domain [[cite:PUB00077868]]. ITM2B (BRI2) is a target of BCL6 transcriptional repression and a short form of the ITM2B protein, similarly to other targets of BCL6, induces apoptosis in hematopoietic cell lines [[cite:PUB00090590]]. ITM2B interacts with amyloid precursor protein (APP) and regulates amyloid beta (Abeta) production [[cite:PUB00090591], [cite:PUB00090592]]. ITM2C (BRI3) also inhibits amyloid precursor protein processing, but through a different mechanism to ITM2B [[cite:PUB00090593]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR10962" "INTEGRAL TRANSMEMBRANE PROTEIN 2"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Integral membrane protein 2", "short" "ITM2"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 1, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 920, "taxa" 3703, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 3831, "sets" 0, "proteins" 3831, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 2681}, "pathways" 1}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR040145", :literature {"PUB00090588" {"URL" nil, "issue" "43", "authors" ["Knight SD" "Presto J" "Linse S" "Johansson J."], "ISO_jour